{"_id":"post-6351603c-22da-479a-8db4-2f8b8f94cc94","_type":"post","title":"Introducing Step Debugging for Python","slug":{"_type":"slug","current":"python-debugger"},"body":[{"_key":"db4ff67cc1a4","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Debug your Python3 programs from your browser","_key":"db4ff67cc1a40"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"h2"},{"_key":"45a31760f590","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"At Repl.it, our goal is to make programming more accessible, and as part of this we aim to provide the full power of popular programming environments with no setup time. And I don't think it's an understatement to say that debugging is the majority of what we, as programmers, do. [](preview end)","_key":"45a31760f5900"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"45b3e1d6a7c4","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"That's why today we're making it possible to step-debug through your Python 3 code right from the browser. We've built a new debug pane that makes it easy step in, out, over, and resume your code. All the common operations a typical debugger would do.","_key":"45b3e1d6a7c40"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"34a840189928","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"34a8401899280","text":"","marks":[]}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"4e563f3c161f","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"To get started:","_key":"4e563f3c161f0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"273552f5c0ec","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"write your code","_key":"273552f5c0ec0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"bullet"},{"_key":"a720fb4ab2bf","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"click the \"debug\" button on the top right corner of the editor","_key":"a720fb4ab2bf0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"bullet"},{"_key":"862831308d0d","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":